    "abstractNote": "The only oriental source considered as related to the Western legend of \u2018Priester John\u2019 is the mention of a \u2018Christian king John\u2019, identified by the Syrian chronicler Bar \u02bfEbroyo (1225-1286) with \u201cOnk Khan\u201d, the ruler of the Kereyids. The article suggests that the identification was inserted by Bar \u02bfEbroyo in his Syriac and Arabic chronicles based on information from European residents at the Ilkhanid court, pointing out significant similarities with William of Rubruck\u2019s report on \u201cRex Iohannes\u201d and \u201cUnc chan\u201d.",
